        <section>
            <h2>What is Cybersecurity?</h2>
            <p>Cybersecurity refers to the practice of protecting systems, networks, and programs from digital attacks. These cyberattacks are usually aimed at accessing, changing, or destroying sensitive information; extorting money from users; or interrupting normal business processes.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Why is Cybersecurity Important?</h2>
            <p>With the increasing reliance on technology, the importance of cybersecurity cannot be overstated. It helps protect personal information, financial data, and national security. As threats evolve, so must our strategies to combat them.</p>
